+| [kubevirt/hyperconverged-cluster-operator#3471](https://github.com/kubevirt/hyperconverged-cluster-operator/pull/3471) | kubevirt/hyperconverged-cluster-operator | CNV-59564 | fix(api): Introduce CommonInstancetypesDeployment configurable |
+
+## BUG ANALYSIS:
+- Root Cause: commonInstanceTypesDeploymentGate was hardcoded in mandatory feature gate list
+- Affected Components: HCO, SSP operator, common-instancetypes
+- Impact: Users unable to disable bundled instancetypes to use custom ones
+- Manifestation: commonInstancetypesDeployment field not available in HCO spec
+
+## TEST STRATEGY:
+Validate that users can control common-instancetypes deployment via HCO CR:
+1. Test disabling common-instancetypes removes resources
+2. Test enabling common-instancetypes deploys resources
+3. Test default behavior is enabled
+4. Test setting persists across HCO reconciliation
+
+## TEST COVERAGE MATRIX:
+- Scenario 1 (P0): Disable common-instancetypes
+- Scenario 2 (P0): Enable common-instancetypes
+- Scenario 3 (P0): Verify default behavior
+- Scenario 4 (P1): Verify persistence across reconciliation
+
+## TEST DATA:
+- Common-instancetypes label selector: instancetype.kubevirt.io/vendor=redhat.com
+- HCO spec field: commonInstancetypesDeployment
+- Valid values: Enabled, Disabled
+
+## ENVIRONMENT REQUIREMENTS:
+- OCP 4.17+ with OpenShift Virtualization 4.17+
+- Standard cluster topology
+- HCO with CommonInstancetypesDeployment field support
+
+## EXECUTION NOTES:
+- Each test scenario uses ResourceEditorValidateHCOReconcile for atomic updates
+- Tests verify both HCO spec and actual resource state
+- Cleanup is automatic via context manager pattern
+"""
